List of block textures

  • Language
  • Watch
  • Edit
See also: Category:Item icons and Category:Block textures
This article uses many images. 
It is not recommended for people with limited or slow internet connections to read through this page.
It has been suggested that this page be split into List of block textures and List of historical block textures. [discuss]
If this split may potentially be controversial, do not split until a consensus has been reached.
Reason: Page is already 120k bytes and sometimes very laggy/unresponsive to load with long load times. Suggest only keeping the "Current textures" on this page, and everything else should move to the new suggested split subpage. Also in 1.21+ there will be more textures to add so this page will get bigger over time. (Upcoming textures stay on this page).
This article is a work in progress. 
Please help expand and improve it. The talk page may contain suggestions.

This page serves as a compact list of all unique block textures which have ever existed in officially released versions of Minecraft. For an overview on when each texture was changed, see the appropriate History of textures subpages.

Original texture files for Java Edition can be downloaded from https://mcasset.cloud/, and the entire default resource pack for Bedrock Edition can be downloaded from https://github.com/Mojang/bedrock-samples/releases

Note: the textures shown in this page are upscaled to 160×160 pixels for display purposes.
